"{\"uid\": \"bangkokpost.com-opinion-opinion-3203860-killing-the-goose-that-lays-the-olympic-gold-medal\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PUBLISHED : 24 Feb 2026 at 01:01  NEWSPAPER SECTION:Oped  WRITER:Nancy Qian  The Olympic Games have always been about more than sports, with the medal count serving as a measure of national vitality.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 65, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nancy Qian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2026 Winter Games in Milan and Cortina are no different.\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.912116651532224e-13, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 235, \"end\": 242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.084912534912364e-15, \"text\": \"Cortina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans, like everyone else, want confirmation of their preeminence.\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 261, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.521198423976376e-18, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So important is that outcome that even US Vice President JD Vance briefly acknowledged the value of non-white immigration to the United States when he complained that Eileen Gu, the US-born medal-winning skier for China, should be competing under the American flag.\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vice_President_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US Vice President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vice_President_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vice_President_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\", \"score\": 0.997291053398998, \"rank\": 0.0027163049226543953, \"text\": \"JD\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\"}, {\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\", \"score\": 0.9999999997999112, \"rank\": 1.9981325910202012e-10, \"text\": \"Vance\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999998716703, \"rank\": 1.2834552082976486e-09, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eileen Gu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\"}, {\"begin\": 550, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999986703187, \"rank\": 9.199211406432813e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.7723609622134803e-12, \"text\": \"American flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the medal table is just one scoreboard.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond the ice rink and the slopes is a much larger and more consequential contest for excellence, namely in scientific leadership, technological supremacy, and geopolitical influence.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, too, China is most portrayed as America's nemesis, with the future of each at stake.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999986703187, \"rank\": 9.199211406432813e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And here, too, there is a question about what role immigrants -- like Gu's Chinese mother -- should play.\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 998, \"end\": 1005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9935181973684333, \"rank\": 0.004989661959523509, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although immigrants bring talent and ambition, they also might compete for jobs or disseminate US-acquired knowledge abroad.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Owing to these concerns, the US has tightened its immigration policies in recent years, even restricting highly skilled professionals.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1183, \"end\": 1185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such measures reflect a fundamental misunderstanding of how countries compete for global pre-eminence -- and the Olympics reveal why.\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Consider figure skating, one of the most visible winter sports.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For decades, the US has crowded the podium with the children of immigrants: Michelle Kwan (silver, 1998; bronze, 2002), Sasha Cohen (silver, 2006), Mirai Nagasu (bronze, 2018, team), Nathan Chen (gold, 2022), and, this winter, Ilia Malinin (gold, 2026, team) and Alysa Liu (gold, 2026).\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1505, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2596191972457502e-13, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sasha Cohen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\"}, {\"begin\": 1636, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mirai_Nagasu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mirai Nagasu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mirai_Nagasu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mirai_Nagasu\"}, {\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nathan Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\"}, {\"begin\": 1715, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilia_Malinin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ilia Malinin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilia_Malinin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilia_Malinin\"}, {\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysa_Liu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alysa Liu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysa_Liu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysa_Liu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same is true in other sports.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1808, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, the speed skater Apolo Ohno (gold, 2002, 2006; eight medals total) has a Japanese-born father, and the snowboarder Chloe Kim (gold, 2018; gold, 2022; silver, 2026) is the daughter of South Korean immigrants.\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apolo_Ohno\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Apolo Ohno\", \"types\": [\"Q847400\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apolo_Ohno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apolo_Ohno\"}, {\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chloe Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\"}, {\"begin\": 2011, \"end\": 2028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_diaspora\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Korean immigrants\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_diaspora\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_diaspora\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The list grows longer if one includes champions descended from earlier migration waves, such as Polish-American Tara Lipinski (gold, 1998) and Japanese-American Kristi Yamaguchi (gold, 1992).\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2127, \"end\": 2142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4675564384838277e-21, \"text\": \"Polish-American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 2143, \"end\": 2156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Lipinski\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tara Lipinski\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Lipinski\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Lipinski\"}, {\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9999999985375325, \"rank\": 1.4626209015807834e-09, \"text\": \"Japanese-American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Time and again, US strength on ice and snow has been built by families whose journeys began elsewhere.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The analogy to science is hard to miss.\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2366, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Roughly 1.2 million international students study in the US each year -- accounting for about 6% of total higher-education enrolment -- and they are concentrated in STEM and quantitative fields.\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2423, \"end\": 2425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2531, \"end\": 2535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2565196978318876e-27, \"text\": \"STEM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, foreign nationals account for 82% of full-time graduate students in petroleum engineering, 74% in electrical engineering, 72% in computer and information sciences, 71% in industrial and manufacturing engineering, 70% in statistics, 67% in economics, 61% in civil engineering, 58% in mechanical engineering and agricultural economics, 56% in mathematics, 54% in chemical engineering, 53% in metallurgical and materials engineering, 52% in materials sciences, and 50% in pharmaceutical sciences.\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 3067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Immigrants and their children also make up a disproportionate share of America's engineers, founders, and patent holders.\", \"from\": 3069, \"to\": 3190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some see this as a source of American strength, whereas critics warn of leakage.\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3220, \"end\": 3228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999412026742442, \"rank\": 5.88007830271657e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, talent flows both ways.\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Among Olympians, for example, the figure skater Deanna Stellato-Dudek was born and trained in the US but now competes for Canada.\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3353, \"end\": 3374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deanna_Stellato\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deanna Stellato-Dudek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deanna_Stellato\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deanna_Stellato\"}, {\"begin\": 3403, \"end\": 3405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3427, \"end\": 3433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999697465687, \"rank\": 2.966068553593304e-08, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More controversially, China reportedly allocated substantial state funding to recruit US-trained athletes such as Gu (who has now won five Olympic medals for her sponsor) and Zhu Yi before the 2022 Beijing Games.\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999986703187, \"rank\": 9.199211406432813e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3610, \"end\": 3616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhu_Yi_(Eastern_Wu)\", \"score\": 0.8425919415519253, \"rank\": 0.14835164835157091, \"text\": \"Zhu Yi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhu_Yi_(Eastern_Wu)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhu_Yi_(Eastern_Wu)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not surprising that such moves fuel anxiety in the US.\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3705, \"end\": 3707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But a sense of perspective is in order.\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The US won 25 medals at the Beijing Olympics in 2022, compared to China's 15, and this gap will be even wider in 2026.\", \"from\": 3749, \"to\": 3867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3753, \"end\": 3755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Evidently, the benefits of attracting foreign talent outweigh the costs.\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The same lesson holds in science, where the US has been the world's leading source of Nobel laureates.\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 4044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3986, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American institutions have captured about 40% of science Nobels since 1945, and over half of economics Nobels since 1969.\", \"from\": 4045, \"to\": 4166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4045, \"end\": 4053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999412026742442, \"rank\": 5.88007830271657e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"America's prize-winning edge has been deeply intertwined with immigration.\", \"from\": 4167, \"to\": 4241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Roughly 40% of US-affiliated Nobel laureates in physics, chemistry, and physiology or medicine have been foreign-born.\", \"from\": 4242, \"to\": 4360, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the private-sector architects of America's most important strategic technologies were also born abroad.\", \"from\": 4361, \"to\": 4472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sergey Brin, born in the Soviet Union, co-founded Google.\", \"from\": 4473, \"to\": 4530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4473, \"end\": 4484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sergey Brin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\"}, {\"begin\": 4505, \"end\": 4510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.505893750861092e-25, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4523, \"end\": 4529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999988650267443, \"rank\": 1.1345455497752912e-06, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elon Musk, born in South Africa, built Tesla and SpaceX.\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4531, \"end\": 4540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 4550, \"end\": 4562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.9266090436572805e-18, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 4570, \"end\": 4575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.696313156314031e-15, \"text\": \"Tesla\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jensen Huang, born in Taiwan, co-founded Nvidia.\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 4636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4588, \"end\": 4600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jensen_Huang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jensen Huang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jensen_Huang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jensen_Huang\"}, {\"begin\": 4610, \"end\": 4616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.2905507934600644e-12, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 4629, \"end\": 4635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nvidia\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eric Yuan, born in China, founded Zoom.\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4637, \"end\": 4646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Yuan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eric Yuan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Yuan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Yuan\"}, {\"begin\": 4656, \"end\": 4661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999986703187, \"rank\": 9.199211406432813e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not new.\", \"from\": 4678, \"to\": 4694, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Immigrants have fuelled America's rise on the global stage since before World War II.\", \"from\": 4695, \"to\": 4780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Albert Einstein fled to the US in the 1930s.\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4781, \"end\": 4787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_I_of_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9971074408208321, \"rank\": 0.00289547294792274, \"text\": \"Albert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_I_of_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_I_of_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 4788, \"end\": 4796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9136373374945317e-32, \"text\": \"Einstein\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\"}, {\"begin\": 4809, \"end\": 4811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John von Neumann, born in Hungary, designed the architecture that underlies modern computing.\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4826, \"end\": 4842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_von_Neumann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.332552350367914e-56, \"text\": \"John von Neumann\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_von_Neumann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_von_Neumann\"}, {\"begin\": 4852, \"end\": 4859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9998083976314966, \"rank\": 0.0001916390508046441, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wernher von Braun, born in Germany and once an engineer for the Nazis, later became the chief architect of the Saturn V rocket that carried Americans to the moon.\", \"from\": 4920, \"to\": 5082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4920, \"end\": 4937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wernher_von_Braun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wernher von Braun\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wernher_von_Braun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wernher_von_Braun\"}, {\"begin\": 4947, \"end\": 4954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.967265901092421, \"rank\": 0.03229095383909544, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 4984, \"end\": 4989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"score\": 0.9529619103421845, \"rank\": 0.04875339998825263, \"text\": \"Nazis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US has repeatedly turned foreign-born talent -- even from rival powers -- into engines of national strength.\", \"from\": 5083, \"to\": 5195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5087, \"end\": 5089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To see why isolation is harmful, ask a simple question: What if America had closed its doors to these brilliant minds?\", \"from\": 5197, \"to\": 5315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Would they have stopped thinking, inventing, and striving?\", \"from\": 5316, \"to\": 5374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course not, just as Ohno and Kwan would not have stopped skating.\", \"from\": 5375, \"to\": 5443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If America turns talent away, talent will not vanish; it will relocate, and another country will claim the medals and the breakthroughs.\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the past year, the number of international graduate students studying in the US declined by 12%.\", \"from\": 5582, \"to\": 5681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5662, \"end\": 5664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If this trend continues, it will undermine America's scientific competitiveness in the long run.\", \"from\": 5682, \"to\": 5778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"International rivalry -- whether on the ice rink or in the laboratory -- is a competition for talent, and it cannot be achieved by hiding from the world.\", \"from\": 5779, \"to\": 5932, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It requires creating the most compelling environment for talent to gather, develop, and remain.\", \"from\": 5933, \"to\": 6028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If the US wants to win the race for science, it must pair the best from abroad with the best at home, and offer not just opportunity but also a country where the best want to be.\\u00a92026 Project Syndicate  Nancy Qian, Professor of Economics at Northwestern University, is Co-Director of Northwestern University's Global Poverty Research Lab, Founding Director of the China Econ Lab, and a visiting professor at the Einaudi Institute for Economics and Finance.\", \"from\": 6029, \"to\": 6485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6036, \"end\": 6038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 6213, \"end\": 6230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Syndicate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Project Syndicate\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Syndicate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Syndicate\"}, {\"begin\": 6232, \"end\": 6242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nancy Qian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\"}, {\"begin\": 6270, \"end\": 6293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.581170360965243e-14, \"text\": \"Northwestern University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_University\"}, {\"begin\": 6313, \"end\": 6336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.581170360965243e-14, \"text\": \"Northwestern University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_University\"}, {\"begin\": 6393, \"end\": 6398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999986703187, \"rank\": 9.199211406432813e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By subscribing, you accept theterms and conditionsin ourprivacy policy.\", \"from\": 6487, \"to\": 6558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To enjoy the full Bangkok Post experience,please disable your ad blocker.\", \"from\": 6560, \"to\": 6633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6578, \"end\": 6590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangkok_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bangkok Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangkok_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangkok_Post\"}]}]}"